# Real .env files (git-ignored by this project's root .gitignore) hold
# secrets and per-environment values — never commit a real one.
#
# Its OWN dedicated schema — deliberately NOT shared with this topic's
# PostgresTransactions example, even though it's a different, unrelated
# table shape. Confirmed directly (2026-07-16): "prisma db push" treats
# its own schema.prisma as the COMPLETE desired state for the whole
# target schema and DROPS anything else living there that it doesn't
# know about — it isn't just a rename risk when shapes coincide, it's
# unsafe to ever point two independent Prisma projects' db push at the
# same schema at all. See build-conventions.md for the full story.
DATABASE_URL="postgres://user:password@host:5432/postgres?schema=node_express_learning_nplusone"
